  "body": "<!-- \r\nBy filing an Issue, you are expected to comply with the Code of Conduct, \r\nincluding treating everyone with respect:\r\nhttps://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md\r\n\r\nNot all sections will apply to all issue types.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nWe run our 10k validators on Ropsten, post-merge, based on Erigon + Teku + Vouch setup.\r\nToday, after upgrading to Erigon 2022.07.02 Teku began crashing.\r\nGoing back to Erigon 2022.07.01 seems to be solving the issue.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n\r\nException stacktrace attached\r\n[extract-2022-07-07T17_58_35.344Z.csv](https://github.com/ConsenSys/teku/files/9066232/extract-2022-07-07T17_58_35.344Z.csv)\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** Successfully publishes attestations\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** Crashes \r\n\r\n**Frequency:** Every 5-10 minutes.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: 22.6.1\r\n* Java version: [`java -version`]\r\n* OS Name & Version: [`cat /etc/*release`]\r\n* Docker Version: [`docker version`]\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: Private cloud",
